summary:
Human breast milk contains diverse microbial communities, primarily composed of *Bifidobacterium* and *Lactobacillus*. These microbes support early infancy immunity and establish a healthy gut environment. 

\boxed{A} Human breast milk does contain microbes; specifically, it harbors commensal bacteria like Bifidobacterium and Lactobacillus which help develop an infant’s immune system and promote a balanced gut microbiome. \boxed{A}

